Long-serving Equity Group Chairman Peter Munga has announced his retirement from the bank after 35 years of service. His position has been taken by current Vice-Chairman David Ansell, who will serve as chairman designate. The bank said Mr Munga, who founded the bank in 1984 as Equity Building Society, expressed his desire to retire from the board as he celebrated his 75th birthday. ALSO READ:

Equity inks deal with Chinese firm